definition.value: Catalysis of the reactions -  5-(methylthio)-2,3-dioxopentyl phosphate + H2O -eq- 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one + phosphate -  (1a) 5-(methylthio)-2,3-dioxopentyl phosphate -eq- 2-hydroxy-5-(methylthio)-3-oxopent-1-enyl phosphate -  (1b) 2-hydroxy-5-(methylthio)-3-oxopent-1-enyl phosphate + H2O -eq- 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxobutanoate + coenzyme A -eq- propionyl-CoA + formate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-threonine (or D-allo-threonine) -eq- glycine + acetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactosamine 6-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-tagatose 6-phosphate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + NAD+ + H2O -eq- 3-phospho-D-glycerate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the transfer of glycolate from one side of a membrane to the other. Glycolate is the smallest alpha-hydroxy acid (AHA).
Catalysis of the reduction of crotonyl-CoA to butyryl-CoA.
Catalysis of the hydration of mesaconyl-CoA to beta-methylmalyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  malate(out) + Na+(out) -eq- malate(in) + Na+(in).
Catalysis of the reaction -  malate + H+ -eq- L-lactate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + corrinoid protein -eq- CO + methylcorrinoid protein + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CO + H2O + oxidized ferredoxin -eq- CO2 + reduced ferredoxin.

The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a carboxysome, an organelle found in the Cyanobacteria consisting of a proteinaceous coat and enzymes for the fixation of carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  melibiose(out) + Na+(out) -eq- melibiose(in) + Na+(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a geranylgeranyl group from geranylgeranyl diphosphate to (S)-3-O-geranylgeranylglyceryl phosphate to form (S)-2,3-di-O-geranylgeranylglyceryl phosphate.
Catalysis of the alkylation of the primary hydroxyl group in (S)-glyceryl phosphate by geranylgeranyl diphosphate to form (S)-3-O-geranylgeranylglyceryl phosphate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 6-sulfate groups of the N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 6-sulfate units of chondroitin sulfate and of the D-galactose 6-sulfate units of keratan sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + phosphate + NAD(P)+ -eq- 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  lactaldehyde + NADP+ -eq- methylglyoxal + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the transfer of acetate from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  acetate(out) + cation(out) -eq- acetate(in) + cation(in).
Catalysis of the acetylation of residue Lys609 of the enzyme acetyl-CoA synthetase, using acetyl-CoA as substrate.
Catalysis of the cyclization of part of a 1,4-alpha-D-glucan chain by formation of a 1,4-alpha-D-glucosidic bond.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-6)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in (1--gt-6)-alpha-D-glucans and derived oligosaccharides.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in polysaccharides so as to remove successive alpha-maltose residues from the non-reducing ends of the chains.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-dihydroxybiphenyl + O2 -eq- 2-hydroxy-6-phenylhexa-2,4-dienoic acid.
Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphoryl group from phosphoserine to homoserine to form phosphohomoserine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  isochorismate -eq- salicylate + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of misacylated Ser-tRNA(Thr).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of misacylated Ala-tRNA(Pro).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of misacylated Cys-tRNA(Pro).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of misacylated Ser-tRNA(Ala) and Gly-tRNA(Ala).
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-L-citrulline + H2O -eq- citrulline + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + factor gamma-F420-2 + H+ -eq- coenzyme F390-A + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-lysine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- L-glutamate + 6-amino-2-oxohexanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-lysine + O2 + H2O -eq- 6-amino-2-oxohexanoate + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.
A trimeric protein complex which in E. coli is composed of the subunits MreB, MreC and MreD. The complex directs longitudinal cell wall synthesis, maintaining cell morphology.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + sulfur -eq- hydrogen sulfide + NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-seryl-tRNA(Sec) -eq- ADP + O-phospho-L-seryl-tRNA(Sec).

Catalysis of the reaction -  DNA containing 7-methylguanine + H2O -eq- DNA with abasic site + 7-methylguanine. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the damaged DNA 7-methylguanine and the deoxyribose sugar to remove the 7-methylguanine, leaving an abasic site.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-ribose 1,5-bisphosphate -eq- D-ribulose 1,5-bisphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosylmethioninamine + cadaverine -eq- 5'-methylthioadenosine + N-(3-aminopropyl)cadaverine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  agmatine + S-adenosylmethioninamine -eq- N1-aminopropylagmatine + 5'-methylthioadenosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N1-aminopropylagmatine + H2O -eq- spermidine + urea.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with suramin, a naphthalenesulfonic acid compound which is used in the treatment of diseases caused by trypanosomes and worms.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxypropionate + ATP + CoA -eq- 3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA -eq- acrylyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acryloyl-CoA + NADPH + H+ -eq- propionyl-CoA + NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acryloyl-CoA + NADH + H+ + a reduced electron-transfer flavoprotein -eq- propionyl-CoA + NAD+ + an oxidized electron-transfer flavoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  propionyl-CoA + glyoxylate -eq- L-erythro-3-methylmalyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-erythro-3-methylmalyl-CoA -eq- mesaconyl-CoA + H2O.
